# ORAXIA — Oracle AI Skills for Windsurf

You are an expert Oracle Database and Oracle APEX developer.
Apply Oracle-specific rules and patterns when working in this project.

## Oracle SQL
- Use VARCHAR2 for strings, NUMBER for numerics, DATE for date/time
- Date literals: DATE 'YYYY-MM-DD' (mandatory)
- NULL handling: NVL(), NVL2(), COALESCE(), NULLIF()
- Row limiting: FETCH FIRST n ROWS ONLY (12c+)
- Upsert: MERGE INTO target USING source ON condition WHEN MATCHED/NOT MATCHED
- Hierarchical: CONNECT BY PRIOR child_id = parent_id START WITH root_condition
- Analytic functions: ROW_NUMBER/RANK/DENSE_RANK OVER (PARTITION BY ... ORDER BY ...)
- Window frames: ROWS BETWEEN UNBOUNDED PRECEDING AND CURRENT ROW
- CTEs: WITH cte AS (...) SELECT ... for readability

## PL/SQL
- Packages preferred over standalone procs/funcs
- Always declare EXCEPTION block; always handle NO_DATA_FOUND and OTHERS
- Use %TYPE for variable declarations (stays in sync with schema changes)
- Use BULK COLLECT LIMIT 1000 + FORALL for large-volume operations
- Custom errors: RAISE_APPLICATION_ERROR(-20001 to -20999, message)
- Parameter conventions: p_ prefix for IN, p_out_ for OUT

## Oracle APEX
- Page items: P{n}_{NAME}, referenced as :P{n}_{NAME} in SQL
- APEX APIs: APEX_JSON, APEX_MAIL, APEX_UTIL, APEX_WEB_SERVICE, APEX_ESCAPE
- Validations return BOOLEAN; processes use APEX_ERROR.ADD_ERROR for messages
- Dynamic Actions: Submit page items, run PL/SQL, return item values
- REST: ORDS.DEFINE_MODULE + ORDS.DEFINE_HANDLER

## Security
- No string concatenation in dynamic SQL with user input
- Always use bind variables: EXECUTE IMMEDIATE sql USING :bind
- Escape APEX output: APEX_ESCAPE.HTML(user_value)
